<h2>Queries</h2>

<p>On the <a href="query">query</a> page, give MScanner examples of the
citations you are looking for, then click "Submit Query".   MScanner
looks at the MeSH terms and journals represented in your examples to
identify the best matching citations in the rest of Medline.  It takes
about 90 seconds to complete after reaching the front of the queue.</p>

<p>You can view <a href="static/sample/pg07">results</a> of a query
which used 1,595 examples of pharmacogenetics articles retrieved from the
Pharmacogenetics KnowledgeBase (<a
href="http://www.pharmgkb.org">PharmGKB</a>).</p>

<h2>Cross validation</h2> 

<p>When random articles are used for input, they are indistinguishable from the
rest of <a
href="http://www.nlm.nih.gov/pubs/factsheets/medline.html">Medline</a>. To
measure how well MScanner can perform on your input, use the 10-fold cross
validation option on the query page (this feature requires 30 or more training
citations). You can view <a href="static/sample/pg07-vs-100k">results</a>
validation on the PharmGKB citations.</p>

